<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Counterfeit2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Counterfeit,</orth> adj. 1) portrayed: <cit><quote>the c. presentment of two brothers,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 4, 54</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) fictitious, false: <cit><quote>a c. assurance,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.4.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 4, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. supposes,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 5.1.120" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 120</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this c. lump of ore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 3.6.39" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 6, 39</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this c. module,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.113" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 113</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a c. stone,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.608" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 608</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) dissembling: <cit><quote>an arrant c. rascal,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a c. cowardly knave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 73</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the c. matron,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 112</bibl></cit>.

<pb n="252" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>